    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/2347a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-29T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. Your attention is directed to paragraph Sixth (<hi rend="italic">l</hi>) of
                    Protocol of April 24, 1934 and the fact that in pursuance thereof, the period
                    for the reception of Memorials by the Embassy terminates at 4 o’clock Tuesday
                    afternoon, June 30. In view of that fact you should designate some members of
                    the staff to be on duty at all times Tuesday to receive and receipt for
                    Memorials up to 4 o’clock but not thereafter. Upon receipt of this telegram
                    please arrange oral understanding with Mexican Agent to above effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
